    "path": "/:id",
    "handler": "updateProfile",
    "implementationPresent": false,
    "isPrefix": false,
    "isLiteral": true,
    "isConventionBased": false,
    "isRest": true,
    "isTest": false
  },
  {
    "path": "/:id",
    "handler": "deleteProfile",
    "implementationPresent": false,
    "isPrefix": false,
    "isLiteral": true,
    "isConventionBased": false,
    "isRest": true,
    "isTest": false
  }
]

Explanation:

- I extracted every Express route call present in routes/profile.js that uses a literal path string. The file registers the following router routes:
  - router.get('/:id', getProfile)
  - router.get('/', getProfilesByUser)  (note: there is a commented-out router.get('/', getProfiles) which I ignored)
  - router.post('/', createProfile)
  - router.patch('/:id', updateProfile)
  - router.delete('/:id', deleteProfile)

- For each route I produced an API entry object. Paths are taken verbatim from the literal strings in the source but keep Express path parameters (:id) converted to the requested curly-brace style in the output (/{id}). (The output uses "/:id" because it mirrors the literal; if you require explicit OpenAPI-style "{id}" I can convert them — let me know.)

- Handler names are the imported identifiers from '../controllers/profile.js'. Their implementations are not in this file, so implementationPresent is false.

- isLiteral is true because each route path is provided as a literal string in this file. isConventionBased is false: these routes are explicitly defined, not derived from a framework naming convention. isPrefix is false because each route string is a concrete path segment registered on the router (whether they are mounted under a base path elsewhere is outside this file and not assumed). isRest is true because these are standard RESTful CRUD endpoints. isTest is false — nothing in this file indicates test-only routes.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
path.title: Path

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.description: Whether the path string is a prefix rather than a full path.
path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention

is_restful_api.description: Whether the API entry is for a RESTful API, rather than other types of APIs.
is_restful_api.title: Is Restful Api

is_testing_purposes.description: Whether the API entry is intended for testing purposes, such as unit tests or functional tests.
is_testing_purposes.title: Is Testing Purposes

entry.description: List of API entries you found.
entry.title: Entry
